about.description:
Decouple helps you to organize your settings so that you can change
parameters without having to redeploy your app.
about.summary: Strict separation of config from code.

name: python-decouple
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "python-decouple" %}
{% set version = "3.2" %}
{% set sha256 = "af87c560a0be614bac1f8609d3a1db35a02b3fa2a4b110e88eeb04e20a0d574a" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt
  noarch: python

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - decouple

about:
  home: https://github.com/henriquebastos/python-decouple/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: '{{ environ["RECIPE_DIR"] }}/LICENSE'
  summary: 'Strict separation of config from code.'
  description: |
    Decouple helps you to organize your settings so that you can change 
    parameters without having to redeploy your app.
  doc_url: https://github.com/henriquebastos/python-decouple/
  dev_url: https://github.com/henriquebastos/python-decouple/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xmnlab
